\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Your name is Mr Bannister. Could I have your Christian names please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 William Herbert.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Aigburth House, Aigburth Vale, Liverpool 17.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Now, your marital status please? Have you been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8196131 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 , or are }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8196131 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Oh, yes. I'm a widower.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Are you thinking of re-marrying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Now, your year of marriage, please.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 1916.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Right. And your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 My birth? 1980 - I'm sorry, 1890.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 And your birthplace, where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 I was born in a street called Lawton Street, by where Lewis's have built over in the city.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Ah really. So that's Lawton Street, Liverpool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 That was - there's only half of it left now - the back half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 And it's all been built over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Built right across. Lewis Cohen was the landlord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Now I'm going to ask you how many year
s did you live in the house where you were born. Now you told me you were born in this pub in Lawton Street, and you lived there nine years, about nine years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Yes. 1890 to about 1901.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 During the Boer War.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Yes. Now where did you live then? Where did you move to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 
We moved to a Benson Street, off Renshaw Street. See, my mother took a boarding house there. Of course, she was a widow, because my father died at 46 or something to that effect, and she took a boarding house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 And how long where you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Well, I've no time. I mean to say, we were there for a few years, and then she took a chip shop in Kensington. We were there a few years.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Well, which house did you live most in? When you were a child, you lived eleven years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 And then we came back to this Benson Street and we were there quite a while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 This was the boarding house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Yes. I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8196131 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 
 from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Yes. Right. Now tell me, which house do you think you lived the longest in as a child?
 Do you think it was Lawton Street, where you lived eleven years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 No, no. In Benson Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 That was the house? Right. Now you moved to Benson Street and then to the Fish }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16267611 &}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511  Chip Shop. Where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 In Kensington.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 In Kensington, and then you moved back to Benson Street and you were there up till 1916.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 
Well there was a period, I'm sorry, there was a period when my mother took a cook's job in a Public House in Great Newton Street, off Pembroke Place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 How long would you have been there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 A couple of years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 So that wasn't the longest place you lived in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 
Right. Now do you remember why the family made these moves? Now you told me previously that you had to move from the Pub where you were born because 
they wanted to build on it and remove the existing buildings. Obviously that was the reason for the move there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Now why did your mother move from Benson Street to the Fish }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16267611 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511  Chip shop? Can you remember why she moved from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 I'll tell you the truth, I don't know whether it was the Fish }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16267611 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511  Chip Shop after Lawton Street now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 It's a long time ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Because that would be ..... why I say that is because that is the time when she would have some of the money left from the Public House.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 So she would have some money to sort of ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 
Well, she had to move there because she had varicose veins badly, and she hadn't the help and she lost practically most of her money - all of her money, in fact. So she came back to Benson Street and took the ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Took the boarding house over again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Now, how many brothers and sisters did you have, Mr. Bannister? How many in your family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Well, I was the only child - my mother }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8196131 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511  twice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10227369 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 I was the only child of her second marriage, so I have no brothers or sisters, only if you you call them half-brothers from my father.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3035053 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7230018\charrsid13375511 Yes. Were they living with you as a child? Where your half-brothers and sisters living with you?
